.TH "nft_validate_register_store" 9 "nft_validate_register_store" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nft_validate_register_store \- validate an expressions' register store
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nft_validate_register_store
.BI "(const struct nft_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "enum nft_registers reg "  ","
.BI "const struct nft_data *data "  ","
.BI "enum nft_data_types type "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
context of the expression performing the load
.IP "reg" 12
the destination register number
.IP "data" 12
the data to load
.IP "type" 12
the data type
.IP "len" 12
the length of the data

Validate that a data load uses the appropriate data type for
the destination register and the length is within the bounds.
A value of NULL for the data means that its runtime gathered
data.
